title: Merge pull request #1051 from jtorrente/current-untidy
message:
Merge pull request #1051 from jtorrente/current-untidy

Adds a bunch of things related to the ListenWithLemur project:

title: Adds a bunch of things related to the ListenWithLemur project:
message:
Adds a bunch of things related to the ListenWithLemur project:
- A component to specify AndroidSettings to improve the experience in mobile devices
- Color changing tweens
- Bunch of effects: addTag, AddToProperty, ChangeParent, RemoveTag, SetSoundVolume, PreloadEntity (for performance)
- Bunch of simple physics components: angular velocity, angular acceleration
- Drag&Drop interaction. Involves Collision events, a sticky component, and a few more things. See DragAndDrop demo

title: Avoid creation of FrameBuffers of 0, 0
message:
Avoid creation of FrameBuffers of 0, 0

The underlying problem is that in the first transition, layout has not
passed through TransitionManager, and its viewport is 0, 0, which is
transmitted to the FrameBuffer constructor. Not the best solution, but
forcing layout before executing the GoScene is not trivial.

title: Added demonstrator to cooldemo.
message:
Added demonstrator to cooldemo.

- change language to spanish to hear "the rain in spain",
a long fragment loaded via Gdx.audio.music

- change language to english to hear a blip,
a short fragment loaded via Gdx.audio.sound

- change bee transparency to alter volume.

title: Added initial sound support
message:
Added initial sound support

- Add sound component to entity to make it play a sound.

- If sound is large, streams via Gdx.audio.music;
if small, loads in-memory via Gdx.audio.sound.
No difference in usage (except less precise isFinished() if small).

- Volume updated via _effects_volume float variable, as modified by
component volume (defaults to x 1.0).

- Cleanup ensured in reset() method, once sound is over.
Gdx.audio.sounds assumed to be up to 2s long.

title: Adding support for conditioned visibility
message:
Adding support for conditioned visibility
- ModelEntities may contain "visbility" model components (Visibility), which just holds an expression that will condition the visibility of the entity on the screen (expression==true?visible:not_visible).
- Visibility components are transformed to VisibilityComponent in the engine through VisibilityProcessor.
- VisibilitySystem processes all VisibilityComponents, checking all the time if the expressions are met. VisibilitySystem extends ConditionalSystem

title: Added JTS library for triangulation and geometry-wise boolean operations
message:
Added JTS library for triangulation and geometry-wise boolean operations

Allows polygons to be merged into (or substracted from) geometries,
which can be triangulated and used to clip arbitrary images.
JTS geometries can also be used for collision-detection using the JTS
"intersects" primitive.

The GeoTester class allows simple testing: left-click to merge polygons
via mouse, right-click to substract polygons.

title: Big refactor concering assets.
message:
Big refactor concering assets.
Now we have a superclass called Assets, abstract, which provides basic functionality for every asset manager in the application

Two classes extends Assets:
- GameAssets deals with assets of the game (for the engine): i18n, images, game.json, sceneXXX.json etc
- ApplicationAssets deals with assets of the application (the editor): skin, i18n, default preferences, etc.

We have also two classes extending GameAssets:
- MockGameAssets: for testing
- EditorGameAssets: extended functionality for game assets in the editor.

title: While we fix #107, which I think it's becoming rather important, I've added a…
message:
While we fix #107, which I think it's becoming rather important, I've added a "FIELD_NAME" constant in several actions where the action name matches the name of the field they are changing. Hopefully this will trim down confussion:

In Actions, the NAME should be referenced from the "views" package.

 the FIELD_NAME should be referenced within the actions package only (e.g. DeleteScene references InitialScene.FIELD_NAME because it may need to change the initial scene of the game).

Issue:

It seems that this change would solve an issue with the callback#finishedLoading
method invocation when the ressource was already loaded.
But still, the callback is never being called.
It's like the resource is never loaded.

How to reproduce the issue:

Go to mockup view/click New project ~> while in the new project view the
Model's project hasn't been initialized nor created.

message: Changed Mockup widget to be resolution independent.

title: Added viewport size values to the Editor.
message:
Added viewport size values to the Editor.
They aren't used in the Desktop version although they are needed for the Mockup in order to achieve resolution independence in all the devices.
For example, let's say I want my Widget to have a width equal to the 20% of the total screen I would set it's preferred width to Editor.getWidth() * 0.2f;
Since we use a virtual viewport in Mockup they replace the traditional Gdx.graphics.getWidth()/Gdx.graphics.getHeight().

title: Basic implementation of text styles. Roughly speaking, all text attributes…
message:
Basic implementation of text styles. Roughly speaking, all text attributes related to how it is rendered (scale, font, color) have been encapsulated into the TextStyle wrapper.

The style of a Text object can be defined directly into the object or through a reference to a file. This allows rapidly changing the appearance of all the text in a game, in one shot, but also personalizing the attributes for a particular piece of text.

Text style is optional. If not set, a basic white, 1.0F style is used.

title: Expression support, including ChangeVar effect
message:
Expression support, including ChangeVar effect
 - Can parse, evaluate and serialize strongly-typed expressions
 - Implements most common operations (easily extensible)
 - Caches constant results to avoid re-evaluation
 - Throws nice exceptions to complain about runtime evaluation problems

Expressions can be built by parsing a lisp-like representation
(see Parser.parse()) or composing Literals, VariableRefs, and Operations

Expressions are evaluated by calling evaluate() on a given VarsContext

title: Adding support for frame-based animations. This is basically a frame renderer defined as follows:
message:
Adding support for frame-based animations. This is basically a frame renderer defined as follows:
- List of frames
     + A frame (TimedRenderer) is a wrapper for any other renderer. It also includes the duration
- Function to determine the sequence of frames
     + Two types are currently supported: linear (with loop/no loop variants) and random. Linear is default, if not specified.

title: Closes #39, closes #37, closes #41; Big refactor in engine Engine has been divided in components:
message:
Closes #39, closes #37, closes #41; Big refactor in engine Engine has been divided in components:

- Assets: to deal with files
- I18N: to deal with i18n (duh)
- SchemaIO: to read pieces of schema from files
- Factory: to convert schema to engine objects
- SceneViewer: a libgdx actor that  represents a scene
- GameController: controls loading games/scenes and variables
- And finally, Engine, that correctly builds all previous components and manages a Stage

The editor is not working right now. We need to rethink some things.

title: A couple of improvements to Video VLC implementation (desktop). This commit is related to issue #34
message:
A couple of improvements to Video VLC implementation (desktop). This commit is related to issue #34
- EngineDesktop has been modified to ensure some good cleaning when the application is closed:
   * It will try to release VLC resources, if created
   * Invokes Gdx.app.exit, instead of calling System.exit directly
Engine.dispose() remains untouched since all these operations seem to be platform-dependent. however, we may want to think a little about setting up a proper dispose protocol (I guess nothing has been really implemented yet)

- I've also wrapped frame.setVisible(true) in EngineDesktop.run() within a SwingUtilities.invokeLater, because in my computer most of the times the Window did not actually show up! This solves that random behaviour
-

title: Improved event managment (and other minor changes)
message:
Improved event managment (and other minor changes)
Event management:
- Added event emitter class, to homogenize all events handling
- Added event emitter for Touch Events
- Added Time event, for events that are produced after a given time
- Added event emitter for Time event
- Updated tech demo to include these events
Other things:
- Added originX and originY to transformations
